QUANTUM-6G VEHICLE OPERATING SYSTEM (Q-6G VOS)

COMPREHENSIVE TECHNICAL SPECIFICATION DOCUMENT

Version: 2.0
Classification: Proprietary & Confidential
Date: October 2024

---

1. SYSTEM OVERVIEW & ARCHITECTURAL PRINCIPLES

1.1 Core Philosophy

Q-6G VOS is a cognitive vehicle framework implementing a continuous autonomous loop: Sense → Predict → Simulate → Constrain → Decide → Act → Learn. The architecture is fundamentally AI-native, quantum-assisted, and 6G-connected, designed to meet ASIL-D (ISO 26262) and ISO 21448 (SOTIF) safety standards while enabling Level 4/5 autonomy.

1.2 Key Design Principles

· Deterministic Real-Time Execution: Hard real-time guarantees (<10ms) for safety-critical functions
· Quantum-Resilient Security: Post-quantum cryptography implemented at all communication layers
· Adaptive Resource Management: Dynamic allocation of compute between perception, decision, and actuation
· Federated Learning Architecture: Distributed model improvement without centralized data pooling
· Graceful Degradation: Multiple fallback modes under sensor/network/compute failure

---

2. DETAILED LAYER SPECIFICATIONS

2.1 LAYER 1: PROACTIVE SENSOR GRID (PSG)

2.1.1 Sensor Specifications

Sensor Type Specifications Update Rate Range Field of View Power
Solid-State LiDAR 1550nm, 256 lines, single-photon sensitive 20 Hz 0.1-250m 120°×25° 18W
Event Camera Array 4× 1280×720, 1.2Mevts/s, 0.1ms latency Continuous (async) 0-100m 140°×100° 8W
Quantum Radar 77-81 GHz, 4D imaging (x,y,z,v), 0.1m/s resolution 50 Hz 0.5-300m ±60° 25W
Ultrasonic Matrix 48× transceivers, 40-70 kHz 10 Hz 0.1-8m 180° hemispherical 5W
6G Antenna Array 8×8 MIMO, 140 GHz, 100 Gbps peak <1ms latency 1000m (LOS) 360° 35W
Interior Sensing 60 GHz radar (vital signs), TOF cameras 30 Hz Cabin Full cabin 6W

2.1.2 Sensor Fusion Requirements

· World Model Update Rate: 100 Hz minimum
· Latency: <20ms from photon to processed object
· Accuracy: 2cm positional, 0.1m/s velocity at 100m
· Environmental Robustness: Operational in rain (≤50mm/hr), fog (visibility ≥10m), snow, -40°C to +85°C

2.2 LAYER 2: MULTI-MODAL FUSION ENGINE (MFE)

2.2.1 Processing Architecture

```
Component           Technology                    Performance
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Primary Processor   Neuromorphic ASIC             10 TOPS @ 15W
Backup Processor    Automotive-grade GPU          5 TFLOPS @ 25W
Memory              LPDDR5X                       64 GB, 200 GB/s
Storage             UFS 4.0                        1 TB, 4 GB/s
```

2.2.2 Fusion Algorithms

· Primary: Transformer-based attention fusion (BERT-like architecture)
· Secondary: Kalman filter banks for object tracking
· Tertiary: Particle filters for uncertainty estimation
· Output Format: OpenLABEL standard with custom uncertainty extensions

2.2.3 Key Performance Indicators

· Object Classification Accuracy: 99.99% for standard ODD objects
· False Positive Rate: <0.001% per km
· Computational Latency: <15ms per fusion cycle
· Power Consumption: <50W peak

2.3 LAYER 3: AI-NATIVE REAL-TIME KERNEL (ARTK)

2.3.1 Kernel Specifications

· Type: Microkernel with hypervisor (Type 1)
· Safety Certification: ISO 26262 ASIL-D, IEC 61508 SIL-3
· Partitions: 8 isolated domains with hardware enforcement
· Scheduling: Priority-based preemptive with time partitioning
· Worst-Case Execution Time: Guaranteed <100µs for highest priority tasks

2.3.2 Resource Management

```
Domain           CPU Allocation   Memory    Criticality   Failure Mode
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Safety Control   30%              512 MB    ASIL-D        Lockstep redundant
Perception       25%              2 GB      ASIL-B        Graceful degradation
Decision         20%              4 GB      ASIL-C        Safe state transition
Networking       15%              1 GB      ASIL-A        Fail-silent
UX/Infotainment  10%              8 GB      QM            Can be sacrificed
```

2.3.3 API Specifications

· Safety-Critical API: AUTOSAR Adaptive Platform 21-11
· AI Model Interface: ONNX Runtime with safety extensions
· Quantum Co-processor Interface: OpenQASM 3.0 + custom extensions
· 6G Network API: 3GPP Release 19 compliant

2.4 LAYER 4: QUANTUM DECISION INTERFACE (QDI)

2.4.1 Hardware Platform

· Primary: Quantum Processing Unit (QPU) - 50 qubit annealer or 32-qubit gate model
· Classical Co-processor: FPGA array for quantum algorithm orchestration
· Memory: HBM2e, 16 GB dedicated
· Interface: PCIe 5.0 x16 (128 Gb/s)

2.4.2 Algorithm Suite

Problem Type Algorithm Qubits Required Execution Time
Trajectory Optimization QAOA (Quantum Approximate Optimization) 24-32 <50ms
Multi-agent Coordination VQE (Variational Quantum Eigensolver) 16-24 <100ms
Emergency Path Planning Grover-Enhanced Search 20-28 <20ms
Energy Routing Quantum Boltzmann Machine 12-16 <200ms

2.4.3 Decision Framework

· Horizon: 15-second forward simulation
· Branching Factor: 1000+ possible futures evaluated per cycle
· Cost Function: Multi-objective with 12 dimensions (safety, comfort, efficiency, legality, etc.)
· Decision Latency: <100ms from scenario input to validated policy output

2.5 LAYER 5: 6G COGNITIVE NETWORK STACK

2.5.1 Radio Specifications

· Frequency Bands: Sub-6 GHz + 28 GHz + 140 GHz carrier aggregation
· Peak Data Rate: 100 Gbps downlink, 50 Gbps uplink
· Latency: 0.1-1ms (air interface), <5ms end-to-end
· Reliability: 99.99999% for safety messages
· Mobility Support: Up to 500 km/h

2.5.2 Network Architecture

```
Network Slice   Bandwidth   Latency   Reliability   Use Case
----------------------------------------------------------------
Safety Critical  100 Mbps   <5ms      99.99999%     V2V collision avoidance
Teleoperation    1 Gbps     <20ms     99.999%       Remote driving
Infotainment     10 Gbps    <50ms     99.9%         AR/VR streaming
OTA Updates      5 Gbps     Variable  99.99%        Software updates
```

2.5.3 Edge Computing Interface

· Protocol: ETSI MEC API compliant
· Compute Offload: Up to 50 TOPS available at edge
· Storage: 1 TB distributed cache per vehicle cluster
· Orchestration: Kubernetes-based with real-time extensions

2.6 LAYER 6: QUANTUM-SECURE COMMUNICATION LAYER

2.6.1 Cryptographic Suite

```
Purpose                    Algorithm               Key Size   Performance
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Key Exchange               CRYSTALS-Kyber          1024-bit   <5ms
Digital Signature          CRYSTALS-Dilithium      2048-bit   <10ms
Symmetric Encryption       AES-256-GCM-SIV         N/A        <1ms/1KB
Hash Function              SHA3-512                N/A        <2ms
QKD Interface              ETSI QKD 014 compliant  256-bit    Variable
```

2.6.2 Security Zones

· Zone 0 (Safety Critical): Hardware-isolated, air-gapped from external networks
· Zone 1 (Vehicle Control): ASIL-D security, PQC protected, intrusion detection
· Zone 2 (Infotainment): Isolated domain with controlled interfaces
· Zone 3 (External): DMZ for V2X communications

2.6.3 Key Management

· HSM: ISO 26262 ASIL-D certified, tamper-proof enclosure
· Key Rotation: Every 24 hours for V2X, every 30 days for internal
· Revocation: Distributed ledger-based certificate authority
· Audit Trail: Immutable logging with quantum-safe signatures

2.7 LAYER 7: APPLICATION & POLICY FRAMEWORK

2.7.1 Application Runtime

· Container Runtime: Docker with real-time extensions
· Orchestration: Kubernetes Automotive (Kauto)
· Sandboxing: gVisor for untrusted applications
· API Gateway: GraphQL with rate limiting and authentication

2.7.2 Policy Engine

```
Policy Type         Language      Enforcement Point    Update Mechanism
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Safety              PULSAR (DSL)  Kernel/Actuators    Manufacturer OTA
Efficiency          Python subset QDI Cost Function   Fleet Learning
Comfort             JSON Schema   Cabin Controller    User Preferences
Regulatory          XML/ASAM ODX  All Layers          Geolocation-based OTA
```

2.7.3 Resource APIs

· Locomotion API: Torque vectoring, suspension control, brake-by-wire
· Energy API: Battery management, solar harvest, V2G integration
· Cabin API: Climate, seating, AR windows, biometric monitoring
· External API: V2X messaging, swarm coordination, infrastructure negotiation

