4. SAFETY & RELIABILITY SPECIFICATIONS

4.1 Safety Mechanisms

· Lockstep Processors: Triple modular redundancy for ASIL-D functions
· Dual/Quad Sensor Redundancy: Cross-validation with voting
· Watchdog Timers: Distributed with escalating responses
· Safe States: 5 defined levels from "Continue with reduced performance" to "Immediate controlled stop"

4.2 Reliability Targets

· MTBF (Hardware): >50,000 hours
· MTTR (Software): <1 hour for non-critical, <5 minutes for critical
· Availability: 99.999% (5 nines)
· Functional Safety: ASIL-D for driving functions, ASIL-B for networking

4.3 Failure Modes & Effects Analysis (Partial)

Component Failure Detection Time Mitigation Degraded Mode
LiDAR failure <100ms Radar/camera fusion Speed reduction 30%
QDI timeout <10ms Classical fallback Conservative driving
6G link loss <5ms 5G/LTE fallback Reduced coordination
Brake actuator fault <2ms Dual redundant Emergency brake via motor

